description:
src/lib.rs:184-189 doc comment:
  /// GCP project IDs allow [a-z0-9-], secret names allow [A-Za-z0-9_-],
  /// and version labels are [A-Za-z0-9]+ or 'latest'.
But the implementation accepts the union [A-Za-z0-9_-] for all three. The doc comment reads like a contract; the implementation deviates without saying so.

Suggested rewrite: either tighten the implementation (preferred — see priority-2 finding 'Validator allows characters GCP rejects in stricter components') or change the comment to explicitly say 'we deliberately accept the union to keep one validator; per-component violations are surfaced as Backend errors at API time'.

Engineering basis: a future contributor reading this doc will reasonably infer per-component validation; their PR adding a project-only rule could break callers who relied on the relaxed behavior. The implementation must agree with the comment.
